## What Is This?

Most affective AI asks: *"what emotion is this?"*
NEPA-HRI asks: *"is this interaction trajectory stable right now?"*

Instead of labeling feelings, NEPA-HRI models human–agent interaction as a
**dynamical system with a formal stability envelope Ω**.

This gives you:
- Measurable, auditable interaction stability metrics
- A control layer between sensing and language output
- Formal derivation of escalation probability P(escalation) and recovery time T_recover
- A foundation for chronic inference in long-term deployments (elderly companionship, support agents, payment flows)

---

## Core Math

Three coupled state variables:

```
E_{t+1} = E_t · exp(-λ) + α · A_t + incident_t + ε  # emotional episode state
S_{t+1} = S_t · exp(-μ) + β · regulation_t + ε      # stability index
δ_t = E_t - E_t^desired                              # affective prediction error
```

**Stability Envelope:**
```
Ω = { (E_t, S_t, δ_t) | |δ_t| ≤ κ · S_t }
```

Inside Ω → Regime A: self-stabilizing, perturbations decay
Outside Ω → Regime B: escalation, cross-frame emotional reactivation

**Measurable metrics:**
```
P(escalation) = P(|δ_t| > κ · S_t)
T_recover = min{ k : S_{t+k} > |δ_{t+k}| / κ }
F_t = Σ w_{t-i} · E_i                (feeling load)
AS_t = F_t - F_{t-1}                 (augmentation score)
VI_t = Var(E_{t-window:t})            (volatility index)
```

